:Namespace test_membership
    ⍝ Failing Test cases to test the testing suite
    ⍝ :Section Failing
    ⍝     Test_Failing01←{1=2∊1 3 4} ⍝ Known incorrect test case
    ⍝ :EndSection

    ⍝ This section of testcases are categorised based on the ⎕DR model.
    ⍝ Read more: https://help.dyalog.com/latest/#Language/System%20Functions/Data%20Representation%20Monadic.htm
    :Section Based on DR
        ⍝D 11	  1 bit Boolean type arrays
        ⍝D 80	  8 bits character
        ⍝D 83	  8 bits signed integer
        ⍝D 160	  16 bits character
        ⍝D 163	  16 bits signed integer
        ⍝D 320	  32 bits character
        ⍝D 323	  32 bits signed  integer
        ⍝D 326	  Pointer (32-bit or 64-bit as appropriate)
        ⍝D 645	  64 bits Floating
        ⍝ 1287  128 bits Decimal
        ⍝ 1289  128 bits Complex

        ⍝ TODO: move assert to utils namespace
        ∇ assert arg
            r←⊃arg
            testName←2⊃arg
            :If r
                'pass ', ⎕dr (3⊃arg)
            :Else
                'fail ', testName, ⎕dr (3⊃arg)
            :EndIf
        ∇
            
        ∇ Test_DR
            bool←0 1 ⍝ 11:1 bit Boolean type arrays
            i1←¯60+⍳120 ⍝ 83: 8 bits signed integer
            ⍝ char1←⎕A ⍝ 80: 8 bits character
            char1←⎕UCS ⍳255 ⍝ 80: 8 bits character
            char2←⎕UCS ⍳10000 ⍝ 160: 16 bits character
            i2←{⍵,-⍵}10000+⍳1000 ⍝ 163: 16 bits signed integer
            char3←⎕UCS ⍳100000 ⍝ 320: 32 bits character
            i4←{⍵,-⍵}100000+⍳1000 ⍝ 323: 32 bits signed  integer
            ptr←2,/⎕A ⍝ 326: Pointer (32-bit or 64-bit as appropriate)
            dbl←{⍵,-⍵}i4+0.1 ⍝ 645: 64 bits Floating
            ⍝ TODO:
                        ⍝ 1287  128 bits Decimal
                        ⍝ 1289  128 bits Complex
            :For data :In bool i1 i2 i4 dbl char1 char2 char3 ptr

                :If 11≠type←⎕DR data

                    assert ((data[?≢data])∊data) 't1' data ⍝ random element is found

                    assert (((((≢data)-1)⍴0), 1)≡data∊(¯1↑data)) 't2' data ⍝ All elements return 0 except last
                    assert (((≢data)⍴1)≡data∊data) 't3' data ⍝ all elements return 1

                    ⍝ Todo: add more tests
                :ElseIf 80≠type←⎕DR data ⍝ because lower does not exist, so it is handled separately
                    assert (~((1⊃data)-1)∊data) 't4' data   ⍝ element outside set is not found

                :Else ⍝ Booleans need special tests
                    ⍝ Boolean tests here because the domain is so small
                    assert (0∊0) 'tb1' data
                    assert (~0∊1) 'tb2' data
                    assert (1 1≡bool∊data) 'tb3' data

                :EndIf
            :EndFor
        ∇
    :EndSection        

